This paper is about Neural Machine Translation (NMT), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the Computer Science category. The paper focuses on testing NMT systems, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). However, the approach proposed in the paper involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper evaluates the approach on real-world datasets, which is a common practice in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper is published in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) section of arXiv, which is a subfield of NLP that deals with the computational aspects of human language. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, and cs.SE, in that order.
